    <h3>Data management</h3>
    <p>In order to visualise a product, we first have to look for the ones of interest in the "Data Management" panel.</p>
    <p>There is a search box at the top that allows filtering based on product name or description as you type in a keyword.<p>
    <p>We have just opened it, you can see it on the right of the screen.</p>
    <p>We also have set a star to both products we will be looking at during this tutorial. This means, they are selected as favourites and in your next visit they will already be available in the "Favourites" panel. Lets look at that panel next.</p>
</section>
<section data-events="ui:open:layercontrol;ui:open:dataManagement">
    <span class="close"><i class="fa fa-times-circle"/></span>
    <h3>Layer Selection</h3>
    <p>Now we have opened the "Favourite Layers" panel and you can see (at least) two Layers, PM10 and UC4_d01_ew_ml_da_PM10surf.</p>
    <p>We will activate both layers in the next step, which will show the data availability in the timeline at the bottom.</p>
    <p>Before we look at the data itself, a short excursion into time and area selection.</p>
    </br>
</section>
<section data-bbox="17.86,28.77,35.86,39.5" data-zoom="5000000.0" data-longitude="27" data-latitude="33" data-layers="PM10;AMIDA_UC4_d01_ew_ml_da_PM10surf_4326_0150897">
